st for me) of the question based on title and the short description provided."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ic4na.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14735,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14735/nandor-poka","reputation":2578,"display_name":"Nandor Poka","accept_rate":75},"score":3,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1428089511,"creation_date":1428089511,"body":"<p>Dendritic cells are so called professional antigen-presenting cells (APCs) as pointed out by Sleepes in comment section. They express both MHC-I and MHC-II receptors on their cell surface on which they present small peptides. These small peptides come from digested proteins of their own (MHC-I) or antigens that were phagocited or taken up by receptor mediated endocytosis (MHC-II). They also express costimulatory molecules necessary for the activation of T-cells (eg. CD80/CD86).<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ReTbP.gif\" alt=\"T-cell activation\">\nsource: <a href=\"http://journals.cambridge.org/fulltext_content/ERM/ERM2_09/S1462399400002143sup004.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://journals.cambridge.org/fulltext_content/ERM/ERM2_09/S1462399400002143sup004.htm<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>As you can see in image above, activation of a T-cell requires two distinct signals: the recognition of an antigen and a co-stimulatory signal.<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/xHmi1.gif\" alt=\"diversification of t-cells\">\nsource: <a href=\"http://www.mhhe.com/biosci/ap/dynamichuman2/content/gifs/0158.gif\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.mhhe.com/biosci/ap/dynamichuman2/content/gifs/0158.gif<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>After activation T-cells undergo rapid division and diversification.<\/p>\n\n<p>Details of T-cell activation by dendritic cells can be found in this article for example:\n<a href=\"http://www.nature.com/icb/journal/v75/n3/pdf/icb199735a.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Immunol Cell Biol. 1997 Jun;75(3):223-30.\nThe role of dendritic cells in T cell activation.\nNi K1, O'Neill HC.<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":31045,"question_id":30994,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/30994/what-is-the-function-of-dendritic-cell-in-immunity","last_activity_date":1428089511,"creation_date":1427978749,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the function of dendritic cell in immunity?","body":"<p>I'm interested in how dendritic cells present antigens to  helper T-cells? I'm also interested in the molecular actions between a dendritic cell and a helper T-cell during the activation of the helper T-cell?  What function does the homing receptor on a T-cell have?<\/p>\n","question_id":30994,"tags":["immunology"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":2,"is_answered":true,"view_count":818,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1428058895},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/YHR1l.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15187,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15187/fzg","reputation":38,"display_name":"FZG"},"closed_date":1428384662,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/476e67c92121154e7910301e56cdfc4c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":948,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/948/mattdmo","reputation":7591,"display_name":"MattDMo","accept_rate":50},"score":2,"post_id":30977,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427920471,"comment_id":51615,"body":"Are you asking about meiosis or mitosis?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/uTYSx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14826,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14826/cagliari2005","reputation":2361,"display_name":"cagliari2005"},"score":1,"post_id":30977,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427930120,"comment_id":51630,"body":"Welcome to SE.biology! These papers <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/ncb/journal/v14/n3/full/ncb2440.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">1<\/a>, <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3626277/\" rel