thinking of would pertain to auto-receptors, not reuptake transporters.  Autoreceptors tend to be more like the post-synaptic targets of the neurotransmitter.<\/p>\n","answer_id":10628,"question_id":10520,"up_vote_count":4},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8a04536099ab016c78d96d5d3c08eb39?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12959,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12959/speedoflight","reputation":70,"display_name":"SpeedOfLight"},"score":-1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":0,"post_id":30923,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427763997,"comment_id":51466,"body":"how does this answer the question?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8a04536099ab016c78d96d5d3c08eb39?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12959,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12959/speedoflight","reputation":70,"display_name":"SpeedOfLight"},"score":0,"post_id":30923,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"edited":false,"creation_date":1427822450,"comment_id":51536,"body":"I am saying that you would most likely overdose and suffer cardiovascular consequences that result in death before it&#39;s possible to have brain damage as a result of too much dopamine in the post-synaptic cleft."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"sc