uct is secreted from the cells. In natural environments ethanol either dilutes in the media bacteria live in or can be taken up by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acetic_acid_bacteria\" rel=\"nofollow\">acetic acid bacteria<\/a> and used as an energy source.<\/p>\n","answer_id":30892,"question_id":30891,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/30891/ethanol-production-by-fermentation","last_activity_date":1427678580,"creation_date":1427666423,"answer_count":1,"title":"Ethanol production by fermentation?","body":"<p>As bacteria are involved in the production of ethanol through fermentation and ethanol is also used as antiseptic that kills bacteria, so <strong>how<\/strong> and <strong>why<\/strong> bacteria are involved in the synthesis of such alcohol which is lethal for itself(bacteria)?<\/p>\n","question_id":30891,"tags":["microbiology","biotechnology"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":30892,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":285,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1427672466},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9505b9216fdae1f6735ed821cfa7e7f8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":14834,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14834/tonja","reputation":238,"display_name":"Tonja","accept_rate":67},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/56b4833d86d3cccc3ccfd6eeaf0b767e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14946,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14946/mdperry","reputation":2645,"display_name":"mdperry"},"score":0,"post_id":30884,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427669248,"comment_id":51408,"body":"Lots of annotated SNPs are located nowhere near  any part of any gene, so you would be quite fortunate to (a) find a SNP that maps close to a gene of interest. It would be even rarer for a public SNP to map in top of a relevant TFBS. If you had some SNPs from an unpublished study that might be cool"}],"an