 of results. <\/p>\n","answer_id":30760,"question_id":30746,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/30746/can-bioluminescence-be-used-for-cancer-or-tumor-detection","last_activity_date":1427475781,"creation_date":1427251732,"answer_count":3,"title":"Can bioluminescence be used for cancer or tumor detection?","body":"<p>What diagnostic applications, if any, are there in using bioluminescence to detect cancer or tumors (in vivo)?<\/p>\n","question_id":30746,"tags":["biochemistry","cell-biology","health","cancer"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":30750,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"too broad","is_answered":true,"view_count":135,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1427475781},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ed56f1240fa17c09d0461c21679dd7dc?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15138,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15138/mimat","reputation":333,"display_name":"mimat"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":30830,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427458600,"comment_id":51237,"body":"Welcome to BioSE. It would be better if you make your question more precise? Disadvantage compared to what? Have you tried an experiment yet?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ed56f1240fa17c09d0461c21679dd7dc?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15138,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15138/mimat","reputation":333,"display_name":"mimat"},"score":0,"post_id":30830,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edi