on the same blot<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>Disadvantages:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>lower sensitivity because the signal is not amplified<\/li>\n<li>only few labels are available<\/li>\n<li>directly labelled primary antibodies tend to be expensive and you need relatively high amounts of them<\/li>\n<li>the labelling can damage or reduce the immunoreactivity of the\nantibody<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p><strong>Indirect Primary-Secondary Antibody systems<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Advantages:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>the secondary antibody amplifies the signal (which is especially\ninteresting for weakly expressed proteins)<\/li>\n<li>differently labelled secondary antibodies can be used on the same\nprimary<\/li>\n<li>primary antibodies from different species can be used simultaneously<\/li>\n<li>one secondary antibody can be used with different primary antibodies\n(for example for the protein of interest and the loading control)<\/li>\n<li>the labelling reaction does not affect the primary antibody<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>Disadvantages:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>cross-reactivity of the secondary antibody can lead to non-specific\nbands<\/li>\n<li>the method takes longer, as more steps in the process are necessary<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>For me the most important point is the higher sensitivity of the indirect method, for comparision see these images (from <a href=\"https://www.lifetechnologies.com/de/de/home/life-science/protein-biology/protein-biology-learning-center/protein-biology-resource-library/pierce-protein-methods/overview-western-blotting.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Life technologies<\/a>):<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/1I5ZP.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/BaH5k.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n","answer_id":30834,"question_id":30830,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/30830/are-there-any-disadvantages-to-hrp-conjugated-primary-antibodies","last_activity_date":1427462165,"creation_date":1427458231,"answer_count":1,"title":"Are there any disadvantages to HRP conjugated PRIMARY antibodies","body":"<p>I need to detect a FLAG tagged protein on a western blot and have to order an antibody. I'm not expecting to see a massive amount of my protein. To keep analysis time to a minimum  I am considering a HRP-conjugated anti-FLAG. Are there any disadvantages to it (e.g. sensitivity)? First hand experiences/problems?<\/p>\n","question_id":30830,"tags":["antibody","western-blot"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":30834,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":311,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1427459384},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c6f0020da083ee1891d4466aa034d775?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":15139,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15139/rick-t","reputation":111,"display_name":"Rick T"},"closed_date":1427475989,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":2,"post_id":30832,"edited":false,"creation_date":1427460676,"comment_id":51242,"body":"duped on <a href=\"http://chemistry.stackexchange.com/questions/27937/can-i-use-my-extech-ph-60-meter-to-measure-soil-ph-if-so-how\" title=\"can i use my extech ph 60 meter to measure soil ph if so how\">chemistry.stackexchange.com/questions/27937/&hellip;<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c6f0020da083ee1891d4466aa034d775?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":15139,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15139/rick-t","reputation":111,"display_name":"Rick T"},"score":0,"post_id":30832,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputat